title: Display property 'none' not taking effect in new PDF emitter
description: When setting the display property of an item to 'none', it does not have the expected effect in the new PDF emitter.
OB: When the display property of an item is set to 'none', it remains visible in the generated PDF.
EB: When the display property of an item is set to 'none', it should be hidden or not displayed in the generated PDF.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Open the application that generates PDFs with the new emitter.
2. Load a document or content that contains an item with the display property set to 'none'.
3. Generate the PDF.
4. Observe that the item with 'display: none' is still visible in the PDF.
